Drag Strip follows Wildrider, "You'll never beat me Wildrider, the 
only thing you will be beating is you head as i speed by, victorious 
as always!" He leaps up following quickly Wildriders lead, 
accelerating quickly, attaining extreme velocities just to catch up 
to his Stunticon friend.

Dead-End, watching from the ship hatch, says knowingly, "Racing 
is pointless, there will always be a winner... yet neither is better 
than the other." Then turning to Motormaster, "My radar map says 
that the ideal place to comence our underwater base construction 
is 23 miles, 23 degrees North by East from our current location."



On 16 Jan 2001, at 8:01, Robert Dahl wrote:

> Motormaster turned to the two stunticons, "okay move out" with those orders
> Wildrider nudged Drag Strip, "Oh boy oh boy oh boy oh boy, looks like we
> finally get some action, eat my dust" with that he leaps forward converting
> util he hits the ground in his car mode, then he starts excellerating to
> 250mph, "ha ha ha, try to keep up ya slow poke" he yells to Drag Strip.
> While seeing this Motormaster puts a hand on his face in dissgust of his
> comrades sanity and stupidity.
